      • parseCmdArguments

        @NotNull
private static @NotNull java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> parseCmdArguments​(@NotNull
                                                                                           @NotNull java.lang.String[] args)
        Transforms an array of program arguments into a \(map : String \to String\). Its keys are option names prefixed by dashes: "i" in "-i" or "a" in "-a", and whose values are values of these options. So, for example, an array ["-h", "-i", "title", "-a", "filename"] will be transformed into a map = { "h" : "", "i" : "title", "a" : "filename", "none" : ""}. As you can see, there is a special key named "none", which point to a value that was passed without any option keys. This method allows only a SINGLE value per option key.
        Parameters:
        args - a string array of program arguments that need to be parsed.
        Returns:
        A map that maps option keys ("-i", "-a", etc.) to their corresponding values.
